body_html: I was looking into this, and I think that is cleaner to have one single export dir per trained graph. You can add a time signature to the export dir '-' and link it to a "last model" directory. Changing the behaviour of the SaveModelBuilder to account for overwrite cases is not worth it.

body: I was looking into this, and I think that is cleaner to have one single export dir per trained graph. You can add a time signature to the export dir '<model-id>-<YYYYHHMM>'  and link it to a  "last model" directory. Changing the behaviour of the SaveModelBuilder to account for overwrite cases is not worth it.
